1175
01:27:00,810 --> 01:27:03,458
In ectopic pregnancies, the baby is often unhealthy.

1176
01:27:03,890 --> 01:27:07,629
On the contrary, the doctor said that her body is also damaged.

1177
01:27:12,598 --> 01:27:13,614
Kian

1178
01:27:14,389 --> 01:27:17,481
You haven't slept since last night

1179
01:27:19,309 --> 01:27:21,325
You don't have to worry about that

1180
01:27:22,575 --> 01:27:23,911
I’m sorry.

1181
01:27:24,475 --> 01:27:28,067
You've become completely weak-hearted.

1182
01:27:29,677 --> 01:27:34,489
I'm sure you hate me.

1183
01:27:34,927 --> 01:27:35,583
Why?

1184
01:27:36,963 --> 01:27:38,137
For my sake

1185
01:27:39,711 --> 01:27:42,989
Hashidara did a lot to me.

1186
01:27:44,520 --> 01:27:46,309
That's enough.

1187
01:27:47,170 --> 01:27:48,590
But

1188
01:27:48,692 --> 01:27:50,567
Let's talk after you get better.

1189
01:27:54,370 --> 01:27:55,785
Hold my hand tightly

1190
01:28:27,340 --> 01:28:28,957
Yoneyan.

1191
01:28:31,184 --> 01:28:32,888
Yoneyan.

1192
01:28:38,559 --> 01:28:39,473
Yoneyan.

1193
01:28:42,220 --> 01:28:44,356
Yoneyan means Itakura.

1194
01:28:46,480 --> 01:28:47,989
Is she dreaming of Itakura?

1195
01:28:49,729 --> 01:28:54,762
As expected, the person she like the most is Itakura-san

1196
01:28:56,040 --> 01:28:59,040
I think that's pretty clear

1197
01:28:59,220 --> 01:29:00,817
Honestly,

1198
01:29:02,061 --> 01:29:07,981
She'll die because of Itakura-san.

1199
01:29:08,348 --> 01:29:10,856
Why you say like that?

1200
01:29:11,709 --> 01:29:14,003
She is having surgery today

1201
01:29:14,107 --> 01:29:15,715
Don't wake her up

1202
01:29:20,763 --> 01:29:22,044
Dawn is almost here

1203
01:30:00,778 --> 01:30:05,873
I feel like I can forgive anything what Koi-san did.

1204
01:30:06,720 --> 01:30:09,720
I think Koi-san just tried her best

1205
01:30:10,990 --> 01:30:13,177
To grab the second happiness.

1206
01:30:13,471 --> 01:30:14,238
To grab the second happiness?

1207
01:30:15,067 --> 01:30:18,980
For her,The first happiness has died.

1208
01:30:19,303 --> 01:30:20,436
About Itakura?

1209
01:30:21,362 --> 01:30:25,643
She worked hard to grab the second happiness.

1210
01:30:26,276 --> 01:30:29,782
I guess She's become unable to distinguish between good and bad things

1211
01:30:31,320 --> 01:30:32,210
It's no wonder

1212
01:30:33,060 --> 01:30:35,338
She was naive by nature.

1213
01:30:36,858 --> 01:30:37,898
Yukiko.

1214
01:30:40,439 --> 01:30:44,724
You turned down a marriage proposal with Mr. Hashidera for the sake of KOI.

1215
01:30:47,143 --> 01:30:48,730
It was not for her.

1216
01:30:50,082 --> 01:30:52,195
A marriage proposal that will be ruined because of her

1217
01:30:53,944 --> 01:30:55,820
I have no regrets at all.

1218
01:30:57,223 --> 01:31:04,687
I want to marry someone who genuinely loves me.

1219
01:31:05,340 --> 01:31:06,342
Is that really true?

1220
01:31:06,580 --> 01:31:07,767
Why?

1221
01:31:08,380 --> 01:31:11,624
I've always wondered about that.

1222
01:31:11,890 --> 01:31:13,258
That's funny.

1223
01:31:14,013 --> 01:31:20,648
I was relieved to hear that, but when I see what Koi-san do

1224
01:31:21,590 --> 01:31:24,590
I sometimes wonder if we're real sisters.

1225
01:31:24,686 --> 01:31:26,249
Don't say anything stupid.

1226
01:31:26,399 --> 01:31:30,411
I don't know what koi-san do.

1227
01:31:47,800 --> 01:31:49,734
I was glad Koi-san was saved.

1228
01:31:52,699 --> 01:31:54,559
At least her life was saved.

1229
01:31:55,563 --> 01:31:57,222
But the child was dead.

1230
01:31:57,874 --> 01:31:59,864
That may not have been my child.

1231
01:32:00,337 --> 01:32:01,397
Can you go to by Tobacco for me?

1232
01:32:03,914 --> 01:32:06,165
I'm not going to threaten her.

1233
01:32:07,317 --> 01:32:10,707
Are you going to marry her to the bartender?

1234
01:32:11,266 --> 01:32:13,164
We'll discuss it together someday.

1235
01:32:13,691 --> 01:32:14,905
He was a sailor.

1236
01:32:15,190 --> 01:32:17,206
I don't know what kind of man he is

1237
01:32:18,128 --> 01:32:19,387
Yes, I have given that much thought

1238
01:32:20,645 --> 01:32:26,323
Ah, I really can't break up with the person I've been with for so long

1239
01:32:26,914 --> 01:32:27,347
But.

1240
01:32:27,469 --> 01:32:30,662
You already knew everything

1241
01:32:32,090 --> 01:32:34,196
These days, I'm struggling to even afford my own money

1242
01:32:35,660 --> 01:32:37,568
Koi has put up a lot of my money.

1243
01:32:37,667 --> 01:32:41,272
Well, I think I've already returned all the various items

1244
01:32:41,966 --> 01:32:43,242
How much money is that?

1245
01:32:43,600 --> 01:32:46,764
How much would you give it from you?

1246
01:32:47,628 --> 01:32:50,442
I am very short of money right now

1247
01:32:52,993 --> 01:32:53,973
Excuse me.

1248
01:32:54,805 --> 01:32:57,805
Hello?
Oh it's you.

1249
01:32:58,870 --> 01:33:00,653
I got a letter from Tokyo

1250
01:33:01,160 --> 01:33:03,330
I had some business to attend to, so I'm sorry

1251
01:33:03,362 --> 01:33:05,378
My sister is coming here next month.

1252
01:33:05,713 --> 01:33:08,309
So I decided to have Yukiko-chan stay here until then

1253
01:33:28,527 --> 01:33:29,340
Miyoshi.

1254
01:33:31,059 --> 01:33:32,458
Here isn't cheap.

1255
01:33:34,009 --> 01:33:37,391
Someone really wanted to meet you.

1256
01:33:42,513 --> 01:33:43,267
Who is this?

1257
01:33:44,184 --> 01:33:45,044
I'm Miyoshi.

1258
01:33:45,618 --> 01:33:47,243
I'm the sister of Taeko

1259
01:33:47,570 --> 01:33:48,443
Why you came here?

1260
01:33:48,850 --> 01:33:50,213
I wanted to meet you.

1261
01:33:50,987 --> 01:33:51,920
For what?

1262
01:33:53,270 --> 01:33:57,874
Did you come to say that you are against me marrying the Taeko?

1263
01:33:58,710 --> 01:34:01,388
If so, what would you do?

1264
01:34:01,810 --> 01:34:02,650
I don't care.

1265
01:34:04,316 --> 01:34:07,671
I have a responsibility to her as a man.

1266
01:34:09,149 --> 01:34:12,682
No matter what anyone says, I will bring her to me.

1267
01:34:14,050 --> 01:34:17,050
If you do that, it's not like that kind of business

1268
01:34:17,720 --> 01:34:19,794
Are you saying you'd like to help pay for her wedding?

1269
01:34:21,702 --> 01:34:22,695
I'll turn down.

1270
01:34:24,150 --> 01:34:27,150
What I want is her, not money.

1271
01:34:28,780 --> 01:34:30,616
This is a place where people like you come,

1272
01:34:31,560 --> 01:34:32,816
so why don't you go home?

1273
01:34:59,023 --> 01:35:00,423
What do you see all the time?

1274
01:35:01,628 --> 01:35:05,750
Big sister, Makioka's house is gone

1275
01:35:05,980 --> 01:35:08,140
and a building like this is going to stand in its place

1276
01:35:08,610 --> 01:35:09,537
Seriously

1277
01:35:10,855 --> 01:35:12,988
the neighborhood has completely changed too.

1278
01:35:13,612 --> 01:35:15,855
I'm disappointed that the town has changed.

1279
01:35:15,948 --> 01:35:17,481
Is everything alright for you?

1280
01:35:17,640 --> 01:35:19,808
I'm not saying it's alright

1281
01:35:19,960 --> 01:35:23,793
I feel like I cry.

1282
01:35:24,526 --> 01:35:26,170
That house was sold

1283
01:35:26,429 --> 01:35:28,302
The house now belongs to the buyer.

1284
01:35:28,740 --> 01:35:31,598
Do you care about anything?

1285
01:35:32,453 --> 01:35:34,741
I thought you would be the one to start crying

1286
01:35:36,130 --> 01:35:39,857
I had a hard time after going to Tokyo. I can't remembered the past.

1287
01:35:42,595 --> 01:35:43,692
Come on, let's go home.

1288
01:35:53,148 --> 01:35:55,705
Are you really going,Koi-san?

1289
01:35:57,041 --> 01:35:58,407
My sister from Tokyo is coming

1290
01:35:58,859 --> 01:36:00,116
I don't wanna see her.

1291
01:36:01,779 --> 01:36:04,779
I'll have to see you again someday, but I can't do it right now

1292
01:36:04,848 --> 01:36:07,408
I don't wanna see her now.

1293
01:36:11,290 --> 01:36:14,290
Please return this to Keibon.

1294
01:36:14,817 --> 01:36:16,192
I lost one of them.

1295
01:36:16,629 --> 01:36:18,046
This is a real pearl.

1296
01:36:21,953 --> 01:36:24,953
Do you think I am really stupid?

1297
01:36:26,390 --> 01:36:27,187
Why?

1298
01:36:29,013 --> 01:36:33,855
Since I met Mr. Itakura, I have understood who I should love.

1299
01:36:35,522 --> 01:36:38,522
But I couldn't forget about luxury.

1300
01:36:42,223 --> 01:36:48,195
I was confused, but I was using Keibon to manipulate money.

1301
01:36:50,992 --> 01:36:52,238
I feel sorry for Keibon.

1302
01:36:54,503 --> 01:36:59,032
If you notice that much, Keibon will forgive you.

1303
01:37:01,002 --> 01:37:02,523
What happened to Miyoshi today?

1304
01:37:03,542 --> 01:37:05,582
He's back in Ashiya and waiting for me.

1305
01:37:06,287 --> 01:37:08,411
He said he'd like to go find a room with me.

1306
01:37:09,130 --> 01:37:10,091
Room?

1307
01:37:11,011 --> 01:37:14,457
He said he wanted to do that.

1308
01:37:15,375 --> 01:37:16,049
I see.

1309
01:37:20,280 --> 01:37:25,160
Koi-san, you really like Miyoshi, don't you?

1310
01:37:26,740 --> 01:37:28,136
Why do you ask that?

1311
01:37:29,955 --> 01:37:31,322
I'm sure if you are with Miyoshi

1312
01:37:32,266 --> 01:37:34,692
You'd be able to endure any hardship.

1313
01:37:37,350 --> 01:37:39,366
You're thinking of renting out the room

1314
01:37:40,530 --> 01:37:42,645
If you do it, you have to make a decision

1315
01:37:43,841 --> 01:37:47,434
Do you doubt us?

1316
01:37:48,985 --> 01:37:50,785
I won't tell you what to say though

1317
01:37:50,810 --> 01:37:52,935
But How good is the other person...

1318
01:37:53,903 --> 01:37:58,489
Can you stand living in poverty?

1319
01:37:59,106 --> 01:38:01,450
You can't do that

1320
01:38:02,505 --> 01:38:03,036
What?

1321
01:38:03,457 --> 01:38:04,684
but he came out and did something wrong

1322
01:38:04,876 --> 01:38:12,418
I'm a dirty woman dating a bad man like bartender.

1323
01:38:13,200 --> 01:38:14,285
Koi

1324
01:38:14,911 --> 01:38:19,551
I think you despise me but I have my own way of life

1325
01:38:20,540 --> 01:38:23,096
From now on, leave me alone

1326
01:38:23,121 --> 01:38:24,348
You don't know my feelings

1327
01:38:24,809 --> 01:38:25,559
Koi.

1328
01:38:31,042 --> 01:38:35,004
why do you say things like that?

1329
01:38:36,430 --> 01:38:38,950
I met Miyoshi.

1330
01:38:39,455 --> 01:38:43,262
I wouldn't do something like that! Honestly if I don't care you.

1331
01:38:43,651 --> 01:38:44,833
Really?

1332
01:38:45,411 --> 01:38:47,403
my sister in the main family was against you.

1333
01:38:47,835 --> 01:38:50,182
I will convince your sister

1334
01:38:51,640 --> 01:38:54,640
My mom came back with her aunt from Tokyo

1335
01:38:55,511 --> 01:38:56,316
so I'll be there soon

1336
01:38:57,480 --> 01:39:00,480
Well then, Koi-san, please wait a moment

1337
01:39:01,010 --> 01:39:04,010
After all, Koi-san was born at the youngest age in a family of only women

1338
01:39:04,700 --> 01:39:07,516
When she was little, she had a pitch black face

1339
01:39:07,540 --> 01:39:10,540
She was called a dirty kid and wasn't loved very much

1340
01:39:11,090 --> 01:39:14,628
So, she don't have to like bartenders

1341
01:39:17,698 --> 01:39:20,050
Welcome.

1342
01:39:20,425 --> 01:39:22,175
Hello?

1343
01:39:22,200 --> 01:39:24,303
you look fine

1344
01:39:24,897 --> 01:39:25,932
I'm just strong.

1345
01:39:27,485 --> 01:39:30,485
I guess you're doing your homework,

1346
01:39:30,573 --> 01:39:31,886
I'll take a look at it.

1347
01:39:35,117 --> 01:39:37,471
Give me the stick.

1348
01:39:38,714 --> 01:39:39,753
Thanks.

1349
01:39:42,987 --> 01:39:48,120
Did you tell your sister about KOI and Miyoshi?

1350
01:39:50,025 --> 01:39:53,025
I was just talking about that

1351
01:39:53,050 --> 01:39:55,619
I feel sorry for myself too.

1352
01:39:56,470 --> 01:39:57,235
Why?

1353
01:39:58,360 --> 01:40:01,766
No matter how much freedom you say you have,

1354
01:40:02,260 --> 01:40:05,657
After all, We need the right man for our home.

1355
01:40:06,454 --> 01:40:07,985
We care about public opinion.

1356
01:40:09,496 --> 01:40:11,368
You are too happy.

1357
01:40:12,210 --> 01:40:13,985
She has no more choices.

1358
01:40:14,502 --> 01:40:16,969
I don't know what kind of person he is.

1359
01:40:17,373 --> 01:40:20,373
Do you know the man

1360
01:40:20,500 --> 01:40:23,500
He's not rich but he's very manly.

1361
01:40:23,820 --> 01:40:26,656
I think she'll be happy with him.

1362
01:40:26,681 --> 01:40:30,266
Yukiko-chan, I agree with this idea.

1363
01:40:30,610 --> 01:40:31,321
Really?

1364
01:40:32,267 --> 01:40:33,845
She is against it.

1365
01:40:34,370 --> 01:40:39,344
The most important thing is personality.
I think our family agree this idea.

1366
01:40:40,380 --> 01:40:44,321
Family background, lineage, and fortune are all gone

1367
01:40:45,462 --> 01:40:47,712
Thanks,Sis.

1368
01:40:50,053 --> 01:40:53,805
But you worry about Koi-san a lot.

1369
01:40:54,500 --> 01:40:57,008
When will you be happy?

1370
01:40:58,321 --> 01:41:03,821
I'm still happy, and I have that feeling in my hearts.

1371
01:41:04,135 --> 01:41:06,071
You can't tell it from the outside.

1372
01:41:06,212 --> 01:41:07,196
Yeah but....

1373
01:41:07,665 --> 01:41:09,118
Don't worry.

1374
01:41:10,180 --> 01:41:13,180
I'll find my happiness for myself,

1375
01:41:15,040 --> 01:41:16,501
I'll bring Koi-san.

1376
01:41:32,563 --> 01:41:35,087
Koi-san?
Koi-san?

1377
01:41:39,353 --> 01:41:40,485
Sorry for keeping you waiting.

1378
01:41:46,743 --> 01:41:48,220
I can't find Koi-san.

1379
01:41:55,498 --> 01:41:58,498
She told me that she met Miyoshi at the station.

1380
01:41:59,540 --> 01:42:00,407
I'm going.

1381
01:42:00,532 --> 01:42:01,845
Hold on.

1382
01:42:04,310 --> 01:42:08,063
I'm talking about money Koi-san wants.

1383
01:42:08,877 --> 01:42:11,877
That is actually what we are keeping

1384
01:42:13,098 --> 01:42:17,204
I used it when my child was sick.

1385
01:42:18,780 --> 01:42:20,555
That's fine.

1386
01:42:21,720 --> 01:42:22,329
Hold on.

1387
01:42:22,560 --> 01:42:24,383
Say this to Koi-san.

1388
01:42:25,376 --> 01:42:29,306
Please tell her that I will pay for your wedding.

1389
01:42:40,259 --> 01:42:41,173
She's coming.

1390
01:43:05,688 --> 01:43:08,429
Your sisters in Tokyo have agreed to your marriage.

1391
01:43:08,454 --> 01:43:09,064
Ok?

1392
01:43:09,890 --> 01:43:11,969
If you find a room, please come back right away.

1393
01:43:12,450 --> 01:43:14,930
We congratulate you.

1394
01:43:15,728 --> 01:43:16,696
Ok?

1395
01:43:24,745 --> 01:43:26,704
Yukiko was on time?

1396
01:43:30,110 --> 01:43:30,931
Sis.

1397
01:43:33,380 --> 01:43:37,226
Come to think of it, it seems my way of thinking is the oldest among my siblings

1398
01:43:39,103 --> 01:43:44,089
It's like there's a disembodied something stuck somewhere in my head forever

1399
01:43:44,735 --> 01:43:45,295
Yeah.

1400
01:43:46,290 --> 01:43:48,942
Sachiko-chan doesn't have any troubles,

1401
01:43:49,074 --> 01:43:52,340
You think so?
I'm sorry.

1402
01:44:02,836 --> 01:44:04,335
Sister, It's snowing.

1403
01:44:05,115 --> 01:44:06,009
Really.

1404
01:44:50,962 --> 01:44:58,665
THE END.

